meanings.definition: To produce more offspring than another organism.
meanings.sent1: The rabbit outreproduces the squirrel in the forest.
meanings.sent2: The bacteria outreproduces rapidly in the petri dish.
meanings.sent3: The ants outreproduce the bees in the garden.
meanings.sent4: The weeds outreproduce the flowers in the garden bed.
meanings.sent5: The fish outreproduces the other species in the pond.

meanings.sent1: The virus outreproduces the immune system in the body.
meanings.sent2: The invasive species outreproduces the native plants in the ecosystem.
meanings.sent3: The mold outreproduces the efforts to clean it from the walls.
meanings.sent4: The pests outreproduce the pest control measures in the house.
meanings.sent5: The bacteria outreproduces the antibiotics in the body.
